language design: Should type fields with runtime type be compared with '=='

Here, the static types of the record's fields are equal, but their
dynamic types may or may not be.  In one case because the indices
described by the domains are different; in the other because the two
arrays might be interpreted as being defined over different anonymous
domains.  How should the compiler-generated ==/!= operators behave in
a case like this?

#28755
